Postpaid phone churn was essentially flat, primarily due to the inclusion of the customer base acquired in the Merger with higher
churn, offset by lower switching activity in the industry due to reduced store traffic due to temporary retail store closures arising
from the Pandemic.
Prepaid churn decreased 79 basis points, primarily due to lower switching activity in the industry due to reduced store traffic due to
temporary retail store closures arising from the Pandemic and the continued success of our prepaid products due to promotional
activities and rate plan offers. (1)
