Free Cash Flow
Free Cash Flow represents Net cash provided by operating activities less cash payments for Purchases of property and equipment,
including Proceeds from sales of tower sites and Proceeds related to beneficial interests in securitization transactions, less Cash
payments for debt prepayment or debt extinguishment. Free Cash Flow and Free Cash Flow, excluding gross payments for the
settlement of interest rate swaps, are non-GAAP financial measures utilized by our management, investors and analysts of our
financial information to evaluate cash available to pay debt and provide further investment in the business.
The table below provides reconciliations of Free Cash Flow and Free Cash Flow, excluding gross payments for the settlement of
interest rate swaps to Net cash provided by operating activities, which we consider to be the most directly comparable GAAP
financial measure.
