Fair Value of Assets Acquired and Liabilities Assumed
We accounted for the Merger as a business combination. The identifiable assets acquired and liabilities assumed of Sprint were
recorded at their estimated fair values as of the acquisition date and consolidated with those of T-Mobile. Assigning fair market
values to the assets acquired and liabilities assumed at the date of an acquisition requires the use of significant judgment regarding
estimates and assumptions. For the estimated fair values of the assets acquired and liabilities assumed, we used the cost, income
and market approaches, including market participant assumptions.
